  "prompt": "Do anti-money laundering regulations exist?",
  "response": "Yes, anti-money laundering (AML) regulations exist in many countries and internationally. These regulations are designed to prevent criminals from disguising illegally obtained funds as legitimate income. Key examples include:\n\n1. United States:\n- Bank Secrecy Act (BSA)\n- USA PATRIOT Act\n\n2. European Union:\n- Anti-Money Laundering Directives (AMLD)\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n\n3. International standards:\n- FATF global recommendations\n- United Nations conventions against financial crime\n\nThese regulations typically require financial institutions to:\n- Verify customer identities\n- Monitor transactions\n- Report suspicious activities\n- Maintain transaction records\n- Implement compliance programs\n\nPenalties for non-compliance can include significant fines and potential criminal charges.",
